<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19357] AsyncConsumer#close hangs during closing because the commitAsync request never completes due to a missing coordinator</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19357</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16103&quot; title=&quot;AsyncKafkaConsumer: Always await async commit callbacks in commitSync and close&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-16103&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-16103&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ensures the AsyncConsumer wait the requests sent by commitAsync during the close. However, the `CoordinatorRequestManager` does not send any request to find coordinator during close, and hence the requests sent by `CommitRequestManager are never completed during the close since there is no coordinator&lt;/p&gt;</description>
